New vehicle sales enjoyed a strong end to the year, according to data from the National Association of Automobile Manufacturers of South Africa (NAAMSA). The group’s data shows that overall vehicle sales over December 2019 totalled 41,698 units – 4.2% better than December 2018, with new cars up 9.1% from a year earlier. For 2019 however, overall sales declined 2.8% to 536,626 units, with car sales down 2.7% to 355,384 units. The top-selling vehicles in December included the usual suspects: The VW Polo, with 1,410 units, was sixth. New to Volkswagen’s line up is the T-Cross, the German car maker’s response to the growing compact crossover sector. The T-Cross was the third-highest SUV brand over December, behind only the Toyota Fortuner, and Ford EcoSport. Kia’s Seltos SUV was the fifth best-seller, having launched in South Africa late last year. Top 10 best-selling SUVs in December 2019 Toyota Fortuner (974 units) – Price from R505,600 <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-337293" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Fortuner-e1566976909864.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" /> Ford EcoSport (837 units): Price from R271,500 <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-287114" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/FordEcosport4-e1543228746199.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="801" /> VW T-Cross (685 units) Price from R343,300 <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-365448" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/VW-T-Cross.png" alt="" width="1048" height="720" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/VW-T-Cross.png 1048w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/VW-T-Cross-300x206.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/VW-T-Cross-1024x704.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/VW-T-Cross-768x528.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 